Terms of Service

Welcome to [COMMUNITY NAME].

This is a public discussion space operated by Commonshub in partnership with the [CREATOR / SHOW NAME] team. It exists to support thoughtful, chronological conversation around their work.

By creating an account or participating in this community, you agree to the following:

1. Purpose of the Community  
This server is designed for serious, good-faith discussion. It is not a platform for harassment, spam, disinformation campaigns, or engagement manipulation.

2. Acceptable Use  
You agree not to:
- Harass, threaten, or intimidate other participants  
- Post unlawful content  
- Engage in coordinated inauthentic behavior  
- Distribute malware or spam  
- Evade moderation actions  

3. Moderation  
This is a moderated community.  
The operators reserve the right to:
- Remove content  
- Suspend or remove accounts  
- Limit access  

when behavior undermines the health of the discussion environment.

4. Public Nature of the Service  
Unless a post is explicitly marked as private or followers-only, content on this server is publicly accessible and may be visible to other federated servers.

5. Federation  
This server is part of the decentralized Fediverse. Content may be shared with other servers unless they are blocked for safety or policy reasons.

6. Service Availability  
This is an evolving pilot environment. Features and availability may change as we improve the service.

7. Contact  
For moderation or legal concerns, contact:  
[MODERATION / ADMIN EMAIL]

By participating here, you are helping build a higher-signal, community-funded public discussion space.
